            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>The text is lightly engraved, and Kaibel's text is based upon a cursory autopsy by Mommsen ('Descripsit festinans, ut ipse ait, Mommsen'); and many of the corrections gaps or other omissions in Kaibel's text are in fact not a true reflection of what is on the stone (see already the better, but previously unpublished, reading of Orsi).</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="line 2"><note>Kaibel: ΖΗΙΑΣ; Orsi: ΖΗΓΑΕ.</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 3"><note>Kaibel: ΛΝΕΛΙΙ; Orsi: ΑΝΕΑΥΤΕ</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 4"><note>Kaibel: bΙΟΝ; Kaibel: ΚΑΛ////</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 5"><note>Kaibel: ·Τ//ΠΑ</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 6"><note>Kaibel: ΑΡΙΟ\ΙΟΥΡΙΤΗ////; Orsi: ΑΡΤΑΛΟΥΡΙΟΥ; Ferrua: ΑΡΤΑΒΟΥΡΙΟΥ</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 7"><note>Orsi: ΑΜΠΡΟΤΑΤΩΝ</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Here lies Paula, having lived 25 years, she lost her life 8 days before the kalends of December (24 November), in the consulship of the illustrious Hierios and Artabourios </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The text was also seen and transcribed by Orsi in the first of his Taccuini, in later 1888. Ferrua already correctly read the name of the consul of 427 CE in line 6 (PLRE II, Ardabur 3), observing that the variant in Arta- is well attested (for Latin Ardabur, Greek Ἀρδαβούριος).</p>
            </div>
